              EventSea is a web application designed to help students find and
              attend events on campus. It provides a more user-friendly and
              visually appealing interface than the current IU Indy event platform,
              <i>The Spot</i>. Users can browse events by category, search for
              specific events, and RSVP to events they are interested in.
            </p>

            <p>
              Future plans for EventSea include adding student orgs to make posts, add a calendar view to the site, and fully develop the app version of EventSea. Our team is also working to begin user testing this semester, with a hope of having a finalized product by Luddy Indianpaolis Capstone on May 1st.
            </p>

            <p>
              This project is my first major project using Svelte, which has been
              a great way for me to learn the framework and its unique features.
              While similar to React in concept, there are enough critical differences that developers should make at least one project in Svelte to understand how it works. In addition, this project has been a great way for me to practice my UI/UX design skills, as the goal of the project is to create a more user-friendly and visually appealing interface than our current event platform.
            </p>

            <p>To stay up to date on EventSea, check out our live build of the site <a target="_blank" href="https://event-sea.vercel.app">Here</a>!
